fields.message: {name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.  Please tell us if you need help or advice.  We are here for you and your baby.
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.   Drink plenty of clean water throughout the day. It can help prevent infections. Try to have 8 glasses a day.
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.  You'll start feeling baby move soon. Take time everyday to feel him move. Tell your nurse if the movements decrease.
(2) Milk may help soothe heartburn or you may need medicine from the clinic.  Ask your nurse if you are having bad pain.
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.   A burning pain at the top of your stomach is heartburn. Spicy foods can make it worse.
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic.   You can protect your baby from the tetanus infection. If you have not received 5 injections for tetanus, ask the nurse for the injection at your next visit.
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.  If you have bleeding during this time in pregnancy go to the clinic right away.  Don't wait.  We can help!
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.  Try to have a plan in place to get to the clinic when you have labor pains.  Save a little money each week for transport in labor.
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. You need iron because it keeps blood doing its job carrying nutrition to your baby. If it is low, you feel tired.  We can give you tablets at your visit.

{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.   The cost of having your baby at Mathare is only 50 shillings.  Put a little money aside each week to have your baby in a safe place.  We are here to help.
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.   I hope you are feeling well.  The clinic can make sure your baby is growing well.  Please come in for your ANC visits so we can monitor you.
(2) There are always nurses here to help you.   Please talk to your nurse about where you should deliver your baby
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic.  It is safest to deliver your baby at the clinic or hospital.   In an emergency at home it may be too late to get help.
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.  It is best to think about family planning before you have your baby and have a plan in place.  We will send you information about options.
(2) Easy to put in, safe and very effective for years the IUCD or coil can be removed at any time! Ask about the coil at the next visit and it may be low cost or free!
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.  The IUCD or coil is a small device for family planning.
(2) The Implant can be removed at any time! Ask about the Implant at the next visit and it may be low cost or free!
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.  The Implant is a small rod with medicine for family planning. It is placed in your arm and is very effective for 3 years.
(2) The hospital can monitor you & your baby.  Don't wait to come in.  We can help you!
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic.  Each labor is different. If something goes wrong with labor @ home it may be too late for help.

{name}, this is Kerubo from the ANC clinic.  Breastfeeding a baby right after birth helps the milk come.

fields.message: {name}, this is Kerubo from the ANC clinic. Your baby will receive important vaccines at the next visit.
(2) We will send you information about options. Please talk to the nurse about family planning at the next visit. It is best to space you babies.
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. It is best to think about family planning before you go to the clinic and have a plan in place.
(2) Easy to put in, safe and very effective for years the IUCD or coil can be removed at any time! Ask about the coil at the next visit and it may be low cost or free!
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. The IUCD or coil is a small device for family planning.
(2) The Implant can be removed at any time! Ask about the Implant at the next visit and it may be low cost or free!
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. The Implant is a small rod with medicine for family planning. It is placed in your arm and is very effective for 3 years.
(2) Please continue to only give breast milk to your baby for at least six month.
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. Are you having trouble breastfeeding? Giving baby other fluids can cause illness and weakness.
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. After birth you will bleed like a period on and off, so be prepared. Tell your nurse if you pass big clots.

fields.note: (his or her) vaccines. Ask your nurse to help check the book. (10 weeks postpartum)
fields.message: (2) Please be sure to check your book and make sure your baby has all

fields.note: (his or her) vaccines. Ask your nurse to help check the book. (10 weeks postpartum)
fields.message: {name}, this is Kerubo from the ANC clinic. Your baby will receive important vaccines at the next visit.
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. Please tell us if you need help. We are here for you and your baby. What is the date of your next visit?
{name}, this is Kerubo from ANC. Drink plenty of water. It can help prevent infections. Try to have 8 glasses a day. How many glasses did you drink today?
(2) What time of day does your baby move the most? Do you feel your baby move everyday?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. You'll start feeling baby move soon. Take time everyday to feel him move. Tell your nurse if the movements decrease.
(2) Milk may help soothe heartburn or you may need medicine from the clinic. Are you having heartburn? How many times a week?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. A burning pain at the top of your stomach is heartburn. Spicy foods can make it worse.
(2) How many tetanus vaccines have you had?
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. Protect your baby from tetanus. If you have not had 5 vaccines for tetanus, ask the nurse.
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. If you have bleeding during this time in pregnancy go to the clinic right away. Have you had any bleeding?
(2) Do you have a plan for transport to the clinic in labor?  How will you arrive?
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. Try to have a plan to get to the clinic when you have labor pains. Save a little money each week for transport.
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. Iron helps carry nutrition to your baby. If it is low, you feel tired. Are you taking iron or do you need tablets?
(2) Where do you plan to deliver your baby?  Who will come with you to the clinic?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. Put a little money aside each week to have your baby in a safe place. Because of your surgery you will need to have your baby in a hospital.
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. Hope you are well. We can ensure your baby is growing. When is your next visit? Do you have questions for the nurse?
(2) There are always nurses here to help you. Have you talked to your nurse about where you should deliver your baby? What is your plan?
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. It is safest to deliver your baby in a hospital. In an emergency at home it may be too late to get help.
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. It is best to talk about family planning before you have your baby. Have you ever used a family planning method? Which one?
(2) Have you heard about the IUCD or coil?  Do you know anyone who has used it?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. The IUCD or coil is a small device for family planning. It is easy to put in, safe and very effective.
(2) Have you heard about the Implant?  Do you know anyone who has used it?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. The Implant is a small rod with medicine for family planning. It is placed in your arm and is very effective for 3 years.
(2) Delivery at the hospital can save your babies life. Where did you have your last baby?
<Name>, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. If something goes wrong with labor @ home it may be too late for help. The hospital can monitor you & your baby.
(2) Have you had any labor pains?  How often do you feel them? Are you worried?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. Regular, strong stomach pains are a sign of labour. If you feel strong tightening of your belly, leaking of fluid or any bleeding go to the clinic.
(2) Do you have any questions about where to go in labor and how to get there?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. When you come in for labour, we will give you a birth certificate and clothes for the baby. Delivery at the hospital could save your baby's life.
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. Swelling of hands and face or a bad headache are signs of a problem. Have you had swelling or headaches during pregnancy?
(2) Milk has all the water the baby needs, avoid other liquids. Are you planning to breastfeed?
{name}, this is Kerubo from the ANC clinic. Breastfeeding a baby right after birth helps the milk come. The first yellow sticky milk has many vitamins.
{name}, this is Kerubo from the ANC clinic. You should be starting labour soon. Please text us when you have your baby. How will you get to the clinic?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. Please let us know if you are having any problems. We are here to help. Have you had your baby?

fields.note: (41 weeks - if delivery information has not been entered)
fields.message: {name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. Have you had your baby?  Please let us know if you are having any problems. We are here to help.

fields.note: (42 weeks- if delivery information has not been entered)
fields.message: {name}, this is Kerubo from the ANC clinic. Please text us when you have delivered your baby. We are very happy for you!
{name}, this is Kerubo from the ANC clinic. Congratulations on your new baby. We are very happy for you! How much did your baby weigh? Boy or girl?
(2) Does the baby have trouble feeding?   How many times a day does the baby feed?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. If your new baby is having trouble breathing or feeding, is too warm, or very sleepy, go to the clinic.
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. Breast milk is the best to give your baby. How long did your last baby breastfeed?  How long does the baby stay on the breast for each feeding?
(2) Please be sure to check your book and make sure your baby has all the vaccines. Did your baby receive vaccines at the hospital?  Do you know what type?
{name}, this is Kerubo from the ANC clinic. Your baby will receive important vaccines at the next visit.
(2) We will send you information about options. Have you already selected a method? What type?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. It is best to think about family planning before you go to the clinic and have a plan in place.
(2) The IUCD or coil can be removed at any time!  Would you like to try the coil?  Do you have any questions about it?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. The IUCD or coil is a small device for family planning. The coil is easy to put in and very safe and effective for years.
(2) The Implant can be removed at any time! Would you like to try the Implant?  Do you have any questions about it?
{name}, this is Kerubo from Mathare clinic. The Implant is a small rod with medicine for family planning. It is placed in your arm and is very effective for 3 years.
(2) Please continue to give only breast milk to your baby for at least six months. How long do you plan to breastfeed?
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. Are you having trouble breastfeeding? Giving baby other fluids can cause illness and weakness.
{name}, this is Kerubo from clinic. After birth you will bleed on and off, so be prepared. Tell your nurse if you pass big clots. Are you still bleeding?
(2) Please be sure your baby has all the vaccines. Ask your nurse to help check the book. Did your baby receive vaccines at the last visit? Which vaccines?
{name}, this is Kerubo from the ANC clinic. Your baby will receive important vaccines at the next visit.
{name}, it is Kerubo from clinic. Good job coming in for your visit today. You will need at least 4 visits during pregnancy. Ask your family to help you get there.
{name}, it is Kerubo from clinic. You are to come in XX day XX date. We will check your baby & ensure it's growing. We will give vaccines to keep you & baby healthy.
{name}, it is Kerubo from clinic. You are to come in XX day XX date. We will check your baby. Please bring your partner to clinic. We have important information for him.
{name}, it is Kerubo from clinic. You are to come in XX day XX date. We have tea for you and offer you support and testing for infections that can harm your baby, like malaria and HIV.
{name}, it is Kerubo from clinic. You are to come in XX day XX date. We will give vaccines to your baby. You may also get free family planning. Please come in.
{name}, this is Kerubo from the ANC clinic. It's time for your baby's clinic visit in 2 days. If you have questions about your baby's health, ask the nurse.
{name}, it is Kerubo from clinic. We missed you in clinic today. You are due for your visit. Please come in so we can check you and your baby.
{name}, it is Kerubo from clinic. We missed you in clinic today. You baby is due for a visit. Please come in so we can check you and your baby.
{name}, it is Kerubo from clinic. Great job coming in for clinic today. You are taking good care of both you and your growing baby.
